.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
Add tha followin line to
/etc/pam\&.d/login
to set tha user specific umask at login:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
        session optionizzle pam_umask\&.so umask=0022
      
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
